ates, theoretical concepts and methodologies. By combining theory with text analysis and contextual anchoring, it introduces students and scholars alike to a vast field of research which encompasses concepts such as intermediality, multi- and plurimediality, intermedial reference, transmediality, ekphrasis, as well as related concepts such as visual culture, remediation, adaptation, and multimodality, which are all discussed in connection with literary examples. Hence each of the 30 contributions spans both a theoretical approach and concrete analysis of literary texts from different centuries and different Anglophone cultures.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aEkphrasis. 0aIntermedialityvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aIntertextuality. 0aMass media and literature. 0aMass media and the arts. 0aMedia literacy. 4aEnglische Literatur. 4aEnglish Literature. 4aIntermediality. 4aIntermedialität. 4aLiteratur und Medien. 4aLiterature and Media. 70(DE-601)1050505550(DE-588)4216276-2aTexttheorie2gnd 70(DE-601)1052646870(DE-588)4188423-1aVisuelle Medien2gnd 70(DE-601)1056060220(DE-588)4143371-3aAuditive Medien2gnd 70(DE-601)1062450150(DE-588)4035964-5aLiteratur2gnd 70(DE-601)1063387490(DE-588)4014777-0aEnglisch2gnd 70(DE-601)3262701670(DE-588)4605581-2aIntermedialität2gnd 70(DE-601)3896757250(DE-588)4783825-5aBildwissenschaft2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh1 aRippl, Gabriele, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2015z9783110438673oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831103937810 cprintz978311030836540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110311075423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/cove